13 fees or commissions paid to, or anticipated to be paid to, issuers, underwriters,
14 placement agents and advisors, financial advisors, remarketing agents, credit
15 enhancers, trustees, accountants, and the counsel of all these persons, bond
16 counsel, and special tax counsel, and shall include the economic benefits
17 received or anticipated to be received by any other persons from any source in
18 return for services performed relating to the issuance of the bonds or notes.
19 (c) Changes in amounts or names of payees or recipients, or additions of amounts
20 or names of payees or recipients, to the listing furnished and made available
21 pursuant to this subsection, shall be furnished to the Capital Projects and
22 Bond Oversight Committee and the Interim Joint Committee on
23 Appropriations and Revenue and made available to the public within three (3)
24 days following the change.
25 (2) The costs required to be furnished under the provisions of subsection (1) of this
26 section shall not include the payment of wages or expenses to full-time, permanent
27 employees of the Commonwealth of Kentucky.
